<p>There are 2 airports in Shanghai, one is located in western part of Shanghai and another is located in the eastern. The western one is <strong>Shanghai Hongqiao Airport</strong>, the eastern one is <strong>Shanghai Pudong International Airport</strong>.</p>

<p>The two airports are far away from each other, if you take drive from Hongqiao to Pudong, it is likely 2 hours+ drive.</p>

<h2>Shanghai Hongqiao Airport</h2>

<p>
<ul>
<li>IATA Airport Code: <strong>SHA</strong></li>
<li>ICAO Airport Code: <strong>ZSSS</strong></li>
</ul>
</p>

<p>You can take <strong>Metro Line 1</strong> to <strong>Xu Jia Hui</strong> and take a taxi to Shanghai Hongqiao Airport, it's about 35 RMB in day and 30% more after 11:00PM.</p>

<h2>Shanghai Pudong International Airport</h2>

<p>
<ul>
<li>Airport Code: <strong>PVG</strong></li>
<li>ICAO Airport Code: <strong>ZSPD</strong></li>
</ul>
</p>

<p>You can take <strong>Metro Line 2</strong> to <strong>Long Yang road</strong> and switch to <strong><a href="http://io.v2ex.com/shanghai/shanghai-meglev-ticket-proce.html" target="_blank">Meglev</a></strong> to Shanghai Pudong International Airport. Meglev is the most modern transportation in the world, its top speed is around 433 KM/H, so it only takes 7 minutes to the airport. The price of Meglev is 50 RMB for single trip, 100 RMB for round trip. If you have a air ticket then the ticket price is 20% off.</p>
